Reporting TeamRobyn Pearce was found dead in her mother's flat in Sea Point on 2 December. (Facebook) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Police were hot on the heels of a suspect in the murder of Stellenbosch University student Robyn Pearce (20) on Wednesday&nbsp;morning (14 December) . Pearce&rsquo;s body was found on 2 December in her mother&rsquo;s flat in Sea Point. The head of the City of Cape Town&rsquo;s Special Investigations Unit, Reynold Talmakkies, said at a media briefing on the City&rsquo;s festive season plans this morning (14 December) that they have followed up on a lead from the community and worked through the night, identifying who the suspect is. They had also identified the blood-stained clothing he was allegedly wearing during the incident as well as the possible murder weapon.It is expected that an arrest will be made soon.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.